en.comp:
A passage is given with 5 questions following it. Read the passage carefully and choose the best answer to each question out of the four alternatives.

My coat's pretty warm, even though it cost £9.99 and came from the flea market. It had a label in it, Christian Dior, but I cut it out as soon as I got home. You can't work where I work and have Christian Dior in your coat. You could have a genuine vintage Christian Dior label. Or something Japanese. Or maybe no label because you make your clothes yourself out of retro fabrics that you source at Alfies Antiques. But not Christian Dior.

As I get near Catford Bridge, I start to feel a knot of tension. I really don't want to be late today. My boss has started throwing all sorts of hissy fits about people "swanning in at all times," so I left an extra twenty minutes early, in case it was a bad day. I can already see: It's a god-awful day. They've been having a lot of problems on our line recently and keep cancelling trains with no warning. Trouble is, in London rush hour, you can't just cancel trains. What are all the people who were planning to get on that train supposed to do? Evaporate?

options.value: Those with the Christian Dior label.

instructions.value: The test contain 4 sections having 100 total questions.&nbsp;
Each question has 4 options out of which only one is correct.
You have to finish the test in 60 minutes.
<p>You will be awarded 2&nbsp;mark for each correct answer and 0.5&nbsp;marks will be deducted for each wrong&nbsp;answer.</p>
There is no negative marking for the questions that you have not attempted.
<p><span style="font-family: arial;">You can write this test only once.&nbsp;</span>Make sure that you complete the&nbsp;test before you submit the test and/or close the browser.</p>
